method.name: when valid file paths are configured, reportFiles returns a list of File objects for each
when invalid file paths are configured, reportFiles returns no File objects
when completedMessage is called, it returns a string message
when post is called, pass parameters to datasource
when post is not activated, then remove remote datasources
when post is activated and there are no remote datasources, show a message
when post is activated and there are uncommitted changes, then remove remote datasources and show a message
when post is activated and there are all changes are committed, then show a message
when there are valid report documents, summaries are generated
when there are invalid report documents, summaries are generated
when the build was successful, the duration summary isSuccessful is true
when the build was not successful, the duration summary isSuccessful is false
when there is a cobertura report file, a coverage map is created
when there is a jacoco report file, a coverage map is created
when there is an invalid jacoco report file, a coverage map is created
when there is an invalid cobertura report file, a coverage map is created
when there is a valid report document, the summary is returned
when a map is created from multiple report files, then the counts of each violation type are accurate
when a pmd map is created, the error count is correct
when plugin is not activated, nothing is posted
when the build finishes unsuccessfully and plugin is activated, post failure status for each type
when the build finishes successfully and plugin is activated, handle success status for each type
when calling split forEach, it prints each item
when calling isNotGreaterThan for two different numbers, regardless of format, the result should be correct
when calling isNotGreaterThan for two identical numbers, regardless of format, the result should be correct
when calling isNotGreaterThan for one number and one null, regardless of format, the result should be correct
when calling isNotLessThan for two different numbers, regardless of format, the result should be correct
when calling isNotLessThan for two identical numbers, regardless of format, the result should be correct
when calling isNotLessThan for one number and one null, regardless of format, the result should be correct
when calling file delete it returns true if the file exists
when usecase is invoked and a summary is not successful, then throw a Gradle Exception with the summary message
when usecase is invoked and a summary is successful, then do nothing
when the plugin is disabled, nothing is posted
when the build is started and the plugin is activated, post a build status
